    "author_association": "MEMBER",
    "body": "# Problem\r\n\r\n- `dictwatcheradd` was originally added as a way to avoid the `options.c`, so we could use global variables instead of options. On the whole that was a reasonable idea, but didn't pan out because `:set` and friends are too ingrained in vim-land, plus the scoping rules of options, are useful despite being insane.\r\n- Lua metatables are much nicer ways to implement dict-watchers.\r\n- dict watchers were never upstreamed to Vim, and probably don't see much usage in plugins\r\n\r\n# Proposal\r\n\r\nRemove `dictwatcheradd` and related functions. \r\n\r\n# Related\r\n\r\n- https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/12544#issuecomment-1116794687\r\n- https://github.com/neovim/neovim/issues/20107",
    "closed_at": null,
    "closed_by": null,
